        public RunInfo(Period duration)
        Creates a new RunInfo.
        Parameters:

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public void start()
        Starts a new measurement run. This resets the iteration counter.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Resets this RunInfo to its original state. If there is a running measurement, a new start time is obtained for the measurement to be able to continue smoothly.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the measurement run.

      • getIteration

        public long getIteration()
        Gets the current iteration counter value. This can be used as an approximate value of passed iterations even though some of them might still be pending their execution.
        Returns:
        Current iteration counter value, -1 if there was no iteration so far.

      • getNextIteration

        public long getNextIteration()
        Gets the next iteration counter value. This automatically increases the iteration counter for the next call to obtain a different value.
        Returns:
        The next available iteration counter value.

      • getRunTime

        public long getRunTime()
        Gets the current measurement run time in millisecond. If the system clock changed during the running measurement, this value will be influenced.
        Returns:
        Current measurement run time.

      • getPercentage

        public double getPercentage()
        Gets the current measurement progress in percents. If the run is limited by time based period and the system clock changed during the measurement, the result value will be influenced.
        Returns:
        Completed percents of the current measurement.

      • getPercentage

        public double getPercentage(long iteration)
        Gets the theoretical measurement progress in percents based on the provided number of passed iterations. If the run is limited by time based period and the system clock changed during the measurement, the result value will be influenced.
        Parameters:
        iteration - The iteration for which we want to know the progress % number compared to the configured period duration.
        Returns:
        Completed percents of the theoretical measurement state. This cannot be more than 100% no matter what value is provided.

      • getStartTime

        public long getStartTime()
        Gets Unix time of the measurement start. If the system clock changed during the measurement, this value will not represent the real start.
        Returns:
        Measurement start time.

      • getEndTime

        public long getEndTime()
        Gets Unix time of the measurement end.
        Returns:
        Measurement end time.

      • isRunning

        public boolean isRunning()
        Is there a running measurement? This is true if and only if isStarted() returns true and we did not reached the final iterations.
        Returns:
        True if the measurement is running.

      • isStarted

        public boolean isStarted()
        Was the measurement started? This is true if and only if start() has been called and there has been no call to stop() since then.
        Returns:
        True if the measurement has been started.

      • getTags

        public Set<String> getTags()
        Gets an unmodifiable set of tags associated with this measurement run.
        Returns:
        An unmodifiable set of tags.

      • hasTag

        public boolean hasTag(String tag)
        Checks for a presence of a given tag.
        Parameters:
        tag - A tag to be checked.
        Returns:
        true if the specified tag is set for this run info.

      • addTag

        public void addTag(String tag)
        Associates a new tag with this measurement.
        Parameters:
        tag - A new tag to be associated.

      • addTags

      • removeTag

        public void removeTag(String tag)
        Removes a tag from this run.
        Parameters:
        tag - A tag to be removed.

      • getScenarioName

        public String getScenarioName()
        Gets the current scenario name. This can carry any useful information. Gets filled by ScenarioLoader to the scenario file name.
        Returns:
        The scenario name.

      • setScenarioName

        public void setScenarioName(String scenarioName)
        Sets the current scenario name. This is useful for reporting to refer to the original scenario file name for example.
        Parameters:
        scenarioName - The name of current scenario.
